data.name: LabelKinDescription.Text
data.value: First pick your Kin! This determines what you look like, what culture you come from, how you look, and even how you might act. Remember this is your character, so your appearance, upbringing, and personality are ultimately up to you so this is just a base. Click on a name for more info about the kin.

data.value: Now you choose a kin attribute to start with. You can start with one attribute of your choice. Once you start playing you can learn up to three depending on the choices your character makes. Click on the info button for the descriptions of the attributes.

data.name: LabelModifierIntro.Text
data.value: We're almost done. This is the modifier page. Modifiers help make your character unique and interesting. Each one adds its own mechanic that you can use to your advantage in some circumstances, or make into a very cool backstory trait. If this isn't something you want to add to your character, just hit common. Common is the same as having no modifier. As always click for info.

data.name: LabelEndIntro.Text
data.value: You did it! Hopefully by this point you have a good image of what you want your character to be. Remeber your character is more than a bunch of stats you just chose. Your character is a personality that you're going to live during events, so make sure they're someone that is exciting for you to be. Someone you can use to escape reality for just a little. The last thing to do is put in your character's name, age, and a description of their backstory and life previous to entering Willshire. You don't need your whole backstory now, just a summary is good. You can always fill out details on your own later. Once you're done with this, go back through and make sure everything is where you want it. You can still change stuff now but once you click "Create Character Sheet" You're done! Thank you for your participation and we can't wait to see you there!

data.name: LabelHalfbreedIntro.Text
data.value: You picked Half-Breed! This means you are half Human kin, half something else. If you picked a Human kin you can pick anything, and if you picked a non human kin then you have to pick a human to round it out. Click the name for info and of course pick something different than you did earlier.
